\begin_layout Section
Background of the Project
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This section states the reasons why the project is being done.
 If the project is related to previous projects, a short history of what
 the previous projects accomplished shall be included.
 If the project is part of a larger work, a brief mention of the rest of
 the work shall be made.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Traffic congestion in the Philippines has always been a big problem.
 Back then, some highways and roads in Metro Manila with the exception of
 EDSA ave.
 has seen a small amount of congestion.
 Now it even reaches places outside the Metro and there are even cases of
 traffic in a large expressways.
 This is due to a large number of vehicle increase in the country.
 According to a statistical study, there already have been 29.4 million vehicles
 since 2013 [8].
 This is a huge number compared to other countries in Southeast Asia whose
 roads have the capacity to handle their total number of vehicles.
 Even schools or areas near them are not exempted from this problem.
 In the UP Diliman Area, some jeepneys have to drive along a section where
 there is a definite congestion of vehicles, which tends to make students
 late for their classes or appointments.
 This section is the CP Garcia.
 It also said that a lot of students would try to bring their own private
 vehicles instead of using public transportation accesible to them, but
 that leads to another problem of shortage in parking spaces in the campus.
 There are more than 3000 parking spaces lacking on all colleges 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "UndergraduateThesis"

\end_inset

.
 That signals the fact that traffic congestion is getting closer to communities
 with inadequate roads.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One of the following solution presented by an advocacy group in UP Diliman
 is to provide accessible bikes for the use of students.
 The group is named UP Bike Share.
 It tries to solve the problem of traffic congestion and the passenger congestio
n in jeepneys especially during the end of classes.
 Like other great ideas this one possesses its own problems, which are the
 loss of bikes.
 As of now bikes are of limited use due to this problem.
 It is because the campus is not practiced biking community.
 Some users do not have the knowledge to lock their bikes properly and that
 could lead to theft.
 Another reason is bikes are able to move in and out of the campus which
 is stricty prohibited, but Bike Share is unable to actually track if some
 bike are leaving the campus.
 Monitoring the bikes is clearly their main problem in terms of risk mitigation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A lot of tracking devices have been present and commercialy accesible like
 GPS.
 Bike Share tries not to use this device since they are power hungry despite
 of it being low cost.
 If GPS were used bikes need to have an immediate station for charging which
 are currently not found inside the campus.
 Instead they have decided to try implementing a wireless mesh network tracking
 system.
 WMN consists of sensor or nodes capable of being tracked in an area.
 It also has low power consumption and sensor are at a low cost.
 There are currently no bike tracking systems present in the country since
 this is one of its few bike sharing projects.
 Because of this, there is a definite demand for development of tracking
 systems not only to help Bike Share but also other projects that requires
 monitoring
\end_layout

