\begin_layout Section
Wireless Technology
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As mentioned above DASH7 is an wireless technology that is an open source
 protocol stack used by Wizzimote.
 It is typically used for wireless sensor networks.
 Compared to other technologies like ZigBee, devices that use DASH7 has
 a wider range spanning up to 2 kilometers which is optimal for an outdoor
 project.
 It is also flexible in such a way that it can also propagate its signal
 for indoors, because DASH7 can penetrate thick walls easily unlike Wifi
 and Bluetooth 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "HT1"

\end_inset

.
 DASH7 is also capable of year long battery life shown on Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:DASH7-Range-and"

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
