\begin_layout Chapter
Formatting Tips
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Inserting Chapters
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the upper left dropdown menu of the LyX window, select 
\shape italic
Chapter
\shape default
.
 You can then type the chapter title that you want.
 Pressing Enter will revert the format to 
\shape italic
Standard
\shape default
, where the content can now be placed.
 Chapters are numbered and placed on the 
\shape italic
Table of Contents
\shape default
 automatically.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Inserting Sections
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the same dropdown menu where you insert a chapter, select 
\shape italic
Sections
\shape default
.
 The sections under the chapter are automatically numbered accordingly.
 These also appear in the generated 
\shape italic
Table of Contents
\shape default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Subsections
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You can also add subsections and subsubsections.
 However, use them sparingly, especially the latter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Inserting Labels
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the chapter/section/image/table that you want to reference, click 
\series bold
Insert > Label
\series default
.
 You can use the default label that LyX generates for you.
 To 'call' it anywhere in your document, click the 
\series bold
Insert > Cross-reference
\series default
.
 This provides an efficient way of pointing out figure/table and chapter/section
 numbers, without the need to type out explicitly what the numbers are in
 the document.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Inserting Floats
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Figures and tables shall be included in the body of the documentation to
 illustrate or clarify the accompanying text.
 Thus, figures and tables must be referenced in the text in order for them
 to be meaningful.
 By convention, figure names should be placed below the image, while table
 names should be placed on top of the table.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moreover, figures or tables should not appear in the document before they
 are mentioned in the text.
 By default, LyX does not follow this rule and places images or tables near,
 but not exactly after, the text referencing it.
 You can force the rule by right-clicking on the 
\shape italic
float:Figure
\shape default
 label in the LyX editor and going to 
\shape italic
Settings
\shape default
.
 In the window that appears, shown in Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Forcing-float-placement"

\end_inset

, uncheck 
\shape italic
Use default placement
\shape default
 and check 
\shape italic
Here definitely
\shape default
 instead.
\end_layout

